Lisa Lewis&rsquo;s ancestral name is Xwemilut. She is a Salish weaver and author of First Nations children&#39;s books.

She apprenticed under master weavers (Chepximiya siyam) Chief Janice George and her husband (Skwetsimltexw) Willard Joseph for 14 years. While she practices the art of Salish weaving, she also learns the songs and protocols that go hand in hand with the artmaking. She weaves regalia to honour ancestors and the people who wear her weaving.  All love and prayers go into her work.

In Lisa&rsquo;s own words, &ldquo;I am honored to be able to share our sacred teachings and be part of our ceremonies. Chen kwen mantumi (I am grateful).&rdquo;
